The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning and self-learning agents for decision making in industrial management, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on the use of these techniques in robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG) for autonomous systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of digital twins, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
